node.text: It’s almost time! I’m all sorts of excited for my @natrellebreastaugmentation tomorrow. My plastic surgeon is going to place the Natrelle INSPIRA® SoftTouch Breast Implants under the muscle… check out Natrelle.com if you want to know what that’s about. I’ll be hanging and watching movies with the kids for a couple of days—which I’m really looking forward to. ❤ #ad

node.text: Okay guys I have always believed transparency is the best way to go. So here goes...I was honestly equally upset about the launch of @jolieandjace because I want the line to be affordable AND quality. Our first run we had someone hand sewing which made the prices way higher.  We have been able to switch manufacturers due to high demand therefore lower costs AND SAME GREAT QUALITY!  so tomorrow we launch the new prices. $30 off on the cozy set!! In the new year I will be making more pieces and will find other materials to create even lower cost pieces so everyone is happy because I want us all to be cozy. ALSO. We have been able to size up to size 18. I will work very hard to continue to be more inclusive in sizes in the new year. I want us to all be cozy and happy. SHOP TOMORROW AT 9am PACIFIC!!!! I’m excited to grow this line with more styles and cozy in 2021 with y’all!  P.s. for the people that bought the first round, check your inbox in the next few days...got something for you;)

node.text: Day 1…..who dis. New beginnings…..When my tattoos speak truth to me but……Okay maybe I do need @tonyrobbins 🤣. @ryanmcpartlin 📸

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jana Kramer on July 22, 2021. May be an image of footwear and outdoors.

node.text: Taking a minute to reflect on set. Today has not been easy and I didn’t know if I would even say anything. If I’m honest I had no idea how I would feel. Relieved? Sad? But I got the “final” call that I’m officially divorced and the tears came.  My first feeling was failure. That I failed my kids. That I was unlovable, not enough. I had moments of anger that I never wanted this for my reality, for my kids.  Let’s just say it was all the feels but here’s what I know….I didn’t fail my kids.  I’m showing them a strong momma and I’ll continue to do that and walk away knowing I did everything I could. This isn’t the end…it’s just the beginning of my story and I’m excited, hopeful, and ready to continue the healing so I can be stronger, and love deeper.  Okay back to work. Love you all! We got this !

node.text:
THE POWER OF A TRIBE. #NatrellePartner 
I’ve been thinking a lot lately about what it means to be independent. And one thing I’ve learned is that being independent doesn’t mean you have to be alone. The last few months would have been impossible if it wasn’t for my tribe. They have been there to celebrate me at my highest and to lift me up at my lowest. They are the voices in my head when I need support, my constant in life, and they are damn fun too. So whatever life throws at you, just remember that you’re not alone, your tribe will always lift you up, will always help remind you of your worth and what you deserve, and you ARE worthy. #thepowerofyou 

This life is meant to be shared and I’m grateful to share it with my tribe.<3

<Swipe left for Important Safety Information.
